decks.notes: The deck focuses on utilizing Aragorn, King of Gondor as the commander in order to maintain a strong aggro strategy. The deck includes a mix of powerful creatures, spells, and lands to quickly build up a board presence and put pressure on the opponent. Cards like Brazen Borrower, Bonecrusher Giant, and True-Name Nemesis help control the battlefield and deal damage efficiently. The deck also includes a range of control spells like Swords to Plowshares, Force of Will, and Counterspell to protect its threats and disrupt the opponent's game plan. By combining aggression with control, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent and secure a quick victory in the 1 vs 1 Duel Commander format.

This deck revolves around aggressive creature-based strategies, utilizing cards that provide a mix of disruption, burn spells, and efficient threats to put pressure on the opponent. The commander, Ghyrson Starn, Kelermorph, supports this game plan by allowing for card draw and additional resources when creatures deal combat damage. The deck includes a mix of countermagic, removal, and versatile creatures that can chip in for damage or provide utility. By keeping the pressure on the opponent and disrupting their game plan with efficient spells, the deck aims to close out games quickly before the opponent can stabilize or answer the threats on the board.
